external_knowledge:
- "captains of their respective ships" refers to employees in higher job titles; 
- "vessels" are the departments where they work;
- "fifth milestone in their career journey" refers to job titles with a job title ID greater than 5;
- "reverse order of their boarding the vessel" implies sorting in descending order based on when they were added (employee ID).

sql:
SELECT d.department_name, sa.average_wage
FROM salary_analysis sa
INNER JOIN departments d ON sa.department_id = d.department_id;

SELECT department_id, year, average_gross_salary
FROM salary_trends
WHERE department_id = 0;
